Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Alhaji Sabo Nanono has said he will ensure that agricultural research institutes in the ministry are strengthened to promote improved seedlings that will galvanize food production in the country. The Minister spoke while receiving briefs from the research agencies under the ministry today in his office. He said, “for me, I want to be very serious with the research institutes so that they will research on improved seeds that will be suitable to our environment.” Suspected bandits kill three, abduct 18 in Kaduna LASG takes responsibility of medical bills of Ikorodu… Brain-dead woman gives birth to baby girl WHO appoints wife of Niger gov as expert on cervical cancer ALSO READ: BREAKING: Buhari approves new NDDC board, Delta man emerges MD The Minister, however, added that the institutes are the engine of growth in the sector. Nanono noted the enormous potentials of Nigerians in many spheres of life and said efforts would be geared towards initiating ways of discovering these potentials especially as they relate to the agricultural sector. The minister urged Nigerians to refocus on making the agricultural sector the hub of economic growth in Nigeria. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
